dct_description_sm: U.S. Geological Survey ; R.B. Marshall, chief cartographer ; A.F. Hassan, cartographer ; compiled in 1911 and 1912 in cooperation with the State of Tennessee ; A.H. Purdue, State Geologist.
Includes inset showing relation of the State of Tennessee to sheets of the Standard Map of the World.
Sheet includes dotted line in center indicating that map can be divided into 2 sheets.
In upper right margin: Western Tennessee.
In center right margin: Eastern Tennessee.
